@Bill
HAWKENONOTATE was my entry to the theme, actually.
I clicked to a rebus theme with [NO]SE, and then realized I could fill neighbouring RHI[NO] with another rebus. That gave me enough of a toehold to go and look at the theme clue again, and I had just enough letters there to see DOUBLE NEGATIVE. Then back to the Des Moines clue, and the realization, from the sparse crossers I had, that NONO was a no-no in that location, but that I could discern the possibility of something ending in (S)TATE. Which gave me the YES substitution, which, with other crosses, made me hazard HAWKE(YES)TATE. Then a couple of confirmatory crosses fell into place, and I was off to the races, albeit at a snail's pace.

